**PropTypes in React are a type-checking mechanism that lets you validate the props passed to a component, ensuring they are of the expected data type.** 
This helps catch bugs early during development, provides console warnings if props are misused, and serves as documentation for how a component should be used.
In modern React, PropTypes are less common because many developers prefer **TypeScript** for static type checking, but they are still useful for smaller projects or when TypeScript isn’t being used.  
