## ⚠️ Limitations & Modern Alternatives
- **Only runs in development mode** (not in production).
- **Does not prevent runtime errors**; it only warns in the console.
- **Deprecated in React core since v15.5**; now requires the `prop-types` package.
- **React 19 removed PropTypes entirely**, so TypeScript or Flow is recommended for long-term projects.  [GeeksForGeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/reactjs/reactjs-proptypes/)  

---

✅ **In short:** PropTypes are a lightweight way to validate props in React, useful for small to medium projects. For larger, production-grade apps, **TypeScript** is the preferred solution because it provides compile-time type safety and better tooling.  

